headline: July PPI, Deere earnings, initial jobless claims: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Thursday, Aug. 14. The Producer Price Index (PPI) for the month of July. Economists are expecting a slight uptick in PPI from the prior month. In the morning, Deere & Company (DE), JD.com (JD), Tapestry (TPR), and Birkenstock (BIRK) will report earnings. Applied Materials (AMAT) will deliver third quarter results in the afternoon, with analysts anticipating sales growth. Initial jobless claims for the week ending Aug. 9 will be released in the morning. Economists expect a slight decrease from the previous week. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: Consumer Sentiment, Retail Sales, Cisco Earnings: Still to Come This Week
summary: The rest of this week brings more economic data, including a report on wholesale inflation on Thursday and retail-sales figures on Friday. Also up ahead are earnings from companies including Deere, network-equipment maker Cisco and Applied Materials.
